assignment2017.codeprovided

Class Connect4GameState

  • java.lang.Object
    • assignment2017.codeprovided.Connect4GameState
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MyGameState

    public abstract class Connect4GameState
extends java.lang.Object
    A class that represents the current state of a Connect4 game, including the configuration of the board and whose turn it is. The class is abstract and is to be extended by your own implementation of all the methods.

    • Method Detail

      • startGame

        public abstract void startGame()
        Starts the game. Initialises every grid position in the board to EMPTY and sets the current turn to RED

      • move

        public abstract void move(int col)
                   throws ColumnFullException,
                          IllegalColumnException
        Drops a counter into a slot on the board. The colour of the counter depends on whose turn it is
        Parameters:
        col - the column in which to drop the counter, in the range 0-6
        Throws:
        ColumnFullException - if the column denoted by col is full (i.e. the move cannot be played)
        IllegalColumnException - if col is not in the range 0-6 (i.e. an invalid column)

      • whoseTurn

        public abstract int whoseTurn()
        Returns whose turn is it
        Returns:
        the constant RED if it is red's turn, else YELLOW

      • getCounterAt

        public abstract int getCounterAt(int col,
                                 int row)
                          throws IllegalColumnException,
                                 IllegalRowException
        Returns a constant denoting the status of the slot at the position denoted by the col and row parameters
        Parameters:
        col - the column of the position being queried (in the range 0-6)
        row - the row of the position being queried (in the range 0-5)
        Returns:
        the EMPTY constant if the slot is empty, the RED constant if the slot is filled by a red counter, the YELLOW constant if is yellow
        Throws:
        IllegalColumnException - if col is not in the range 0-6 (i.e. an invalid column)
        IllegalRowException - if col is not in the range 0-5 (i.e. an invalid row)

      • isBoardFull

        public abstract boolean isBoardFull()
        Returns whether the board is full and the game has ended in a tie
        Returns:
        true if the board is full, else false

      • isColumnFull

        public abstract boolean isColumnFull(int col)
                              throws IllegalColumnException
        Returns whether the column denoted by the col parameter is full or not
        Parameters:
        col - the column being queried (in the range 0-6)
        Returns:
        true if the column denoted by col is full of counters, else false
        Throws:
        IllegalColumnException - if col is not in the range 0-6 (i.e. an invalid column)

      • getWinner

        public abstract int getWinner()
        Indicates whether the game has been won, and by whom
        Returns:
        the constant EMPTY if there is no winner yet, else the constant RED if the red player has four in a row, or the YELLOW constant if it is yellow that has won

      • gameOver

        public abstract boolean gameOver()
        Indicates whether the current game has finished
        Returns:
        true if there is a winner or the board is full

        Copies the current Connect4GameState instance into another object
